1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7002 of Title 70, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability
5 shall promulgate rules establishing a micro-credential for certified
6 teachers who complete Certified Academic Language Therapist (CALT)
7 certification or Center for Effective Reading Instruction (CERI).
8 B. The requirements for a CALT micro-credential or a CERI
9 micro-credential shall include at a minimum:
10 1. A master’s degree;
11 2. Completion of a comprehensive therapy-level training;
12 3. Successful passage of a CALT competency examination or CERI
13 competency examination; and
14 4. Twenty-eight (28) days of instruction post the passage of
15 the applicable competency examination.
16 C. A certified teacher who earns a CALT micro-credential or a
17 CERI micro-credential shall be authorized to screen students for and
18 identify characteristics of dyslexia.
19 D. A micro-credential awarded pursuant to this section shall be
20 reflected on a teacher’s certificate to teach.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
22 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
